cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new type of convolutional neural network (CNN) architecture for image processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the benefits of the proposed architecture in terms of compression, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of the Discrete Cosine Transform (DCT) filters for image compression suggests that the paper could be relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed architecture in image segmentation and edge detection, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
